Byline: Times(Times)

MUSCAT Eoe1/4" Oman Club and Alargan Towell Investment have signed a memorandum of understanding (MoU) to develop the club.

The objective is to upgrade the facilities of the club to have state-of-the-art sporting facilities. Alargan Towell is planning to develop the commercial and the residential section within the club.

Oman Club is one of the oldest clubs in the Sultanate and was established in 1942. The club has won His MajestyEoe1/4aos Cup for Hockey in 2008, and His MajestyEoe1/4aos Cup for Football in the years 1979 & 1994.

Alargan Towell is a joint venture between Alargan International Real Estate Company (KSC), a Kuwaiti-based company; and W.J.Towell & Co of Oman.

The company has recently launched the Qurm Gardens Project, which is due for completion in early 2010.

The company has a track record of successful completion of projects in Oman Eoe1/4" Alargan Homes in Al Mawaleh and Al Hail Homes.

The company mainly concentrates on middle-income housing. Alargan TowelEoe1/4aos achievements in real estate and property development have been widely recognised by prestigious industry awards.

Apart from CNBC Award, Alargan Towel won the Best Residential Developer Award Eoe1/4" 2005, from Euromoney and the Best Developer in Oman Eoe1/4"2006 and 2008, by International Real Estate Finance (IREF). These awards reaffirm the commitment of the company to be the premium real estate developer in the Arabian Gulf region.
